1.22
log
@- document how to set ipsec stuff running at boot
- remove hazy tcp md5 blurb

ok hshoexer
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
.\"	$OpenBSD: ipsecctl.8,v 1.21 2006/08/31 19:01:16 ho Exp $
a43 19
.Pp
When the variable
.Va ipsec
is set to
.Dv YES
in
.Xr rc.conf.local 8 ,
the rule file specified with the variable
.Va ipsec_rules
(by default
.Pa /etc/ipsec.conf )
is loaded automatically by the
.Xr rc 8
scripts.
The keying daemon,
.Xr isakmpd 8 ,
can also be enabled to run at boot time via the
.Va isakmpd_flags
variable.
@


